Order and Collect Orders
When you place an order through The Franco Manca Application Services, a payment confirmation email will be sent, with a receipt.
Please ensure you provide an accurate contact telephone number to ensure we can reach you in case of problem.
Orders placed outside the operating hours can only be placed for future orders, where you chose your selected time slot.
You should not consider that your order has placed and accepted unless you receive an order confirmation via email. There is no minimum for orders from Franco Manca pickup services.
If your you want to place a large order or order more than 6 pizzas, you must call and discuss your order with the restaurant directly.
You should contact the restaurant directly in the below circumstances:
If your order is taking longer than expected;
If you have a query about your order;
If you wish to change or cancel your order (although this may not be possible if the order is already in progress);
If you will not get to the restaurant from which you chose to collect your order, you will still be charged for the meal.
If there is any problem with your order when collecting it, please talk to our restaurant manager at the restaurant that you specified to collect your order from.
All menu items are subject to availability. If the product is not available to purchase, it will be disabled on the service or you will be notified on the telephone or in person.
If one of the products in your order becomes unavailable after and order has been confirmed, we will contact you on the telephone or in person.
We endeavour to get our food ready for you to collect at your chosen time slot, per the product description and to the correct temperature. In the event that something goes wrong and is within our control, we will do everything we can to rectify the situation.
If Order and Collect Service is oversubscribed at a certain time, Franco Manca will notify you that the kitchens are at maximum capacity and that an order cannot be placed at this time.
If you wish to change or cancel your order after it has been accepted and authorized, you should contact the restaurant from which you have chosen to pick up your order
.
However, there is no guarantee that we will be able to agree to your request as the order may already be in progress.
We may cancel any order due to unforeseen circumstances and will inform you if we do this. You will not be charged for any orders we cancel. If payment has already been taken for an order we cancel, you will usually be reimbursed using the same method you used to pay for your order.
All meals and products are subject to availability.
Franco Manca Loyalty Scheme
Each Franco Manca Loyalty Scheme promotion will have rules associated with the promotion. These rules are liable to change at any time.
The stamps or rewards earned in the Franco Manca Loyalty Scheme have no cash value. The stamps or rewards are personal to you and may not be sold, transferred or assigned to, or shared with family, friends or others under any circumstances. If your stamps or rewards are lost, stolen or destroyed, they cannot be exchanged or refunded.
Stamps or rewards may have an expiry date. Please check the terms for each promotion to confirm the expiry dates. Stamps or rewards beyond the expiry date will not be exchanged, refunded or extended.
Unfortunately at the moment only Franco Manca pizzeria located in the United Kingdom are participating in the Franco Manca Loyalty Scheme.
Once you have enrolled in the Franco Manca Loyalty Scheme through the Mobile and Web Application, for every six stamps you earn you will receive a free reward redeemable for a free main course pizza or main course salad of your choice (“Free Pizza Reward”) when dining in at a participating UK Franco Manca pizzeria. Your Free Pizza will be automatically loaded onto your account and will be available to you for 12 months. Your Free Pizza Reward may not be redeemed alongside any other reward, offer or voucher and it expires after 12 months.
To earn stamps in the Franco Manca Loyalty Scheme:
Dine in a Franco Manca pizzeria: each diner that checks in to their table with the Mobile and Web Application and buys a full priced main course pizza or main course salad will earn one stamp;
Order a takeaway through the Franco Manca Order and Collect system: earn one stamp for each order that consists of at least one fully priced main course pizza or main course salad;
Order a takeaway at a Franco Manca pizzeria (including all orders at Franco Manca Stratford), by phoning ahead, by walk in ordering or order a delivery through Uber Eats: earn a stamp for each 8 digit code at the bottom of a Franco Manca paper receipt entered through the “Add a Stamp” function on the Mobile and Web Application; The maximum number of stamps that maybe earned by you using the “Add a Stamp” function is limited to 2 per day.
Welcome promotion: earn one welcome stamp for all new users registering on the Mobile and Web Application;
Students: earn 2 bonus student stamps on each journey of six stamps if you are validated as a student (“Verified Student”);
Invite a friend: earn a stamp and a free drink when you invite a friend to register on the Mobile and Web Application using your invitation code and that friend checks in and purchases their first main course pizza or main course salad. The maximum number of stamps that can be earned through invite a friend is limited to ten per calendar month. The referrer and referee will each earn a stamp, but only the referrer will earn a free drink. Free drinks are not valid at Franco Manca in Scotland or Wales, where referrers are instead entitled to a free dessert.
To qualify as a Verified Student, when you next dine in a Franco Manca pizzeria, check in to the table and present your original student identification to a member of staff to validate your student status. Once you are classified as a Verified Student, this status will remain on your account until the first anniversary of the validation date. Once expired, you may validate again through the same process if you are still a student.
Franco Manca reserves the right to unregister or make ineligible for the Franco Manca Loyalty Scheme any user account that has been inactive for two consecutive years. Inactive is defined as no purchase activity.
Franco Manca reserves the right to terminate, discontinue, cancel or amend the Franco Manca Loyalty Scheme at any time and in its sole discretion without notice to you.
Order and Pay in Restaurant
